Date:  1/2/1862
Source:  Otago Daily Times
Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  The Government was patriarchal, and was divided into three classes, all of which were frequently represented by one person, viz.: The prophet, the charmer, and the hereditary head of the tribe, who was "taboo" or sacred; in fact, the institution of the "taboo" was interwoven with all their institutions, and the penalty for breaking it was death.
